article.headline: Hampton 73, Radford 69
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Jeff Granger and Bruce Brown each scored 18 points as Hampton beat Radford 73-69 Tuesday night. Brown grabbed 11 rebounds for Hampton (1-4), which came back from a 31-27 halftime deficit for the win. The Pirates outrebounded Radford (5-3) 44-35. Hampton led 17-7 in second-chance points, but the Highlanders were better off the fast break, outscoring Hampton 14-2. Hampton's bench outscored Radford's 26-13, fueled by Granger's 18. Chris Oliver led Radford with 17 points and 11 rebounds. Whit Holcomb-Faye added 16, and Martell McDuffy had 13. Matthew Williams had 15 points for Hampton.
